job_desc:
About the job
Purpose & Overall Relevance For The Organisation

Global Business Services (GBS) aims to provide globally unified services based on standardized and automated solutions across different functions and markets. This will enable us to drive operational efficiency, quality services, improved agility and better decision-making whilst reducing complexity and workload.

Our Direct-to-Consumer (DTC) team handles large volumes of data and has a direct impact on the company's financial results. The selected person will be responsible for raw data gathering and handling from various sources to interpret patterns and trends. Responsible for managing data sets, developing reports and troubleshooting data issues. Responsible for scrutinizing the information using data analysis tool and reporting it to operational teams and management.

Key Responsibilities

Collect and interpret DTC data;
Analyzing results from data collected;
Report the results to management and business;
Identifying patterns and trends in data sets;
Defining new data collection and analysis processes;
Identify processes improvements from analysis performed;
Providing technical expertise on data storage structures, data mining, and data cleansing.

Key Relationships

GBS DTC eComm leadership team
DTC eComm GPO team
DTC eComm teams
Local finance markets

Knowledge, Skills And Abilities

Ability to transform big datasets into comprehensive and insightful information for the DTC;
Curious and analytical mindset with a special focus on problem-solving and root cause analysis;
VBA, PowerQuery, and Advanced Excel skills are required;
SAP and PowerBI knowledge are considered as a plus;
Ability to read, write and communicate in English in a business setting;
Strong verbal and written communication skills;
Curious and growth mindset; keen to learn and approach subjects outside of comfort zone, look beyond the obvious;

Qualifications

University degree in Finance, Math’s, Statistics, or equivalent experience ;
3+ years relevant work experience in the business analysis area;
Broad and deep theoretical understanding of job function.

